23
00:01:36,040 --> 00:01:38,940
=Episode 17=

24
00:01:39,500 --> 00:01:40,340
Mom.

25
00:01:40,340 --> 00:01:42,900
Western food…
isn't really appropriate, is it?

26
00:01:43,020 --> 00:01:44,380
I mean, it's a birthday,

27
00:01:44,620 --> 00:01:46,620
we need a spinning round table, right?

28
00:01:46,780 --> 00:01:48,300
Chinese food feels more fitting.

29
00:01:48,780 --> 00:01:49,980
What birthday?

30
00:01:49,980 --> 00:01:50,980
Whose birthday?

31
00:01:51,180 --> 00:01:52,780
My birthday is in September!

32
00:01:53,020 --> 00:01:54,140
Are you losing your mind?

33
00:01:55,940 --> 00:01:58,220
Jianjun called and said

34
00:01:58,460 --> 00:01:59,980
that he and Jianguo

35
00:01:59,980 --> 00:02:02,300
are bringing my grandkids

36
00:02:02,300 --> 00:02:04,100
from the U.S. to Shanghai.

37
00:02:05,140 --> 00:02:06,300
They even named it

38
00:02:06,540 --> 00:02:08,020
the "Roots-seeking Tour."

39
00:02:08,020 --> 00:02:08,900
Pretty fancy, right?

40
00:02:09,860 --> 00:02:12,420
They're coming all the way from overseas,

41
00:02:12,580 --> 00:02:14,100
so I need to show some face.

42
00:02:14,620 --> 00:02:15,460
We should treat them

43
00:02:15,780 --> 00:02:17,020
to a proper meal.

44
00:02:17,300 --> 00:02:18,740
The Oriental Pearl will be perfect.

45
00:02:18,740 --> 00:02:19,220
I love it.

46
00:02:21,020 --> 00:02:22,820
So, the money you're giving me

47
00:02:22,820 --> 00:02:25,060
is because your beloved sons
are coming back,

48
00:02:25,460 --> 00:02:28,220
and you want me to use it
to book a restaurant, right?

49
00:02:28,220 --> 00:02:29,060
Exactly.

50
00:02:29,300 --> 00:02:30,380
I don't want to do it.

51
00:02:32,500 --> 00:02:33,780
Why?

52
00:02:34,460 --> 00:02:36,120
It's just booking a restaurant.

53
00:02:36,120 --> 00:02:37,420
What's there to be unhappy about?

54
00:02:38,420 --> 00:02:40,660
Mom, Qian Kang's back
is in terrible shape,

55
00:02:40,860 --> 00:02:42,820
and I'm out
searching for a job every day.

56
00:02:42,820 --> 00:02:44,580
At the employment agency,

57
00:02:44,820 --> 00:02:46,220
I'm treated like a rotten cabbage,

58
00:02:46,220 --> 00:02:47,820
picked over and thrown aside.

59
00:02:47,820 --> 00:02:49,140
I've gotten so many dirty looks!

60
00:02:49,580 --> 00:02:50,860
Don't you care about any of this?

61
00:02:51,020 --> 00:02:51,980
All you care about is...

62
00:02:52,620 --> 00:02:55,100
"My precious sons are coming back!"

63
00:02:55,980 --> 00:02:56,820
Right?

64
00:03:07,100 --> 00:03:08,420
At the end of this month,

65
00:03:08,500 --> 00:03:11,020
her nominal age is going to be 45.

66
00:03:11,300 --> 00:03:12,420
When you mentioned a meal,

67
00:03:12,420 --> 00:03:14,380
she thought you were
celebrating her birthday.

68
00:03:14,860 --> 00:03:15,700
What month is it now?

69
00:03:16,140 --> 00:03:16,980
March!

70
00:03:17,660 --> 00:03:18,500
Oh no.

71
00:03:20,020 --> 00:03:21,020
Oh no,

72
00:03:21,020 --> 00:03:22,060
this is really bad.

73
00:03:22,380 --> 00:03:23,220
Qian Kang.

74
00:03:25,900 --> 00:03:26,740
This is terrible.

75
00:03:26,780 --> 00:03:27,820
I really forgot.

76
00:03:27,820 --> 00:03:28,660
I completely forgot.

77
00:03:28,660 --> 00:03:29,500
I'm so sorry.

78
00:03:36,700 --> 00:03:37,620
Maddening, huh?

79
00:03:39,020 --> 00:03:40,420
Can you see how maddening this is?

80
00:03:41,220 --> 00:03:42,380
In that family,

81
00:03:42,620 --> 00:03:43,900
in her heart,

82
00:03:44,620 --> 00:03:46,300
only her two sons

83
00:03:46,520 --> 00:03:47,710
are her real children.

84
00:03:48,220 --> 00:03:49,700
Only their matters

85
00:03:49,700 --> 00:03:50,980
are important.

86
00:03:51,820 --> 00:03:53,220
The whole world should

87
00:03:53,220 --> 00:03:54,220
revolve around them.

88
00:03:55,500 --> 00:03:56,780
Maybe Chairwoman Liao

89
00:03:57,460 --> 00:03:59,220
didn't mean it like that?

90
00:04:00,380 --> 00:04:01,420
If she didn't,

91
00:04:02,560 --> 00:04:03,780
then what else could she mean?

92
00:04:05,300 --> 00:04:06,660
Even if she did,

93
00:04:06,720 --> 00:04:08,780
her favoritism isn't something
that just started.

94
00:04:08,780 --> 00:04:09,860
Her two sons…

95
00:04:10,820 --> 00:04:12,460
Well, Xiu'e…

96
00:04:12,460 --> 00:04:14,020
Pei didn't mean it like that.

97
00:04:14,420 --> 00:04:16,380
She… She just wants to comfort you.

98
00:04:17,020 --> 00:04:19,260
Look, if you lower your expectations,

99
00:04:19,380 --> 00:04:20,780
you'll feel better.

100
00:04:20,780 --> 00:04:21,900
Your heart will feel lighter.

101
00:04:22,820 --> 00:04:23,660
Just think about

102
00:04:23,900 --> 00:04:25,060
how my husband treats me,

103
00:04:25,060 --> 00:04:26,620
and how your husband treats you.

104
00:04:26,740 --> 00:04:27,980
If I compared the two,

105
00:04:28,220 --> 00:04:29,820
I'd have been driven crazy long ago.

106
00:04:31,100 --> 00:04:33,060
But your husband is capable.

107
00:04:33,900 --> 00:04:36,220
Qian Kang is a good husband.

108
00:04:37,220 --> 00:04:38,420
But now,

109
00:04:39,100 --> 00:04:40,780
with his back problems,

110
00:04:40,860 --> 00:04:41,940
I'm not sure

111
00:04:42,260 --> 00:04:43,980
what he'll do

112
00:04:44,380 --> 00:04:46,380
if he has to stop driving a taxi.

113
00:04:46,980 --> 00:04:48,380
Don't be so pessimistic.

114
00:04:48,660 --> 00:04:50,260
Qian Kang is still young,

115
00:04:50,260 --> 00:04:51,660
and he'll be fine.

116
00:04:53,100 --> 00:04:54,300
True, at least he's younger

117
00:04:54,300 --> 00:04:55,460
than Zhang Qiming.

118
00:04:56,780 --> 00:04:58,060
But Zhang Qiming

119
00:04:58,380 --> 00:04:59,780
doesn't have back problems...

120
00:05:02,900 --> 00:05:03,740
What...

121
00:05:04,180 --> 00:05:05,580
What are you doing?

122
00:05:10,220 --> 00:05:11,060
Pei,

123
00:05:11,340 --> 00:05:12,540
your husband's back

124
00:05:12,900 --> 00:05:13,780
seems really good!

125
00:05:14,870 --> 00:05:15,900
I work in the pharmacy.

126
00:05:15,900 --> 00:05:17,280
I can get any medication you need.

127
00:05:17,420 --> 00:05:18,260
Need anything?

128
00:05:20,820 --> 00:05:21,660
No.

129
00:05:21,900 --> 00:05:22,740
Listen,

130
00:05:22,860 --> 00:05:23,700
I...

131
00:05:24,100 --> 00:05:25,620
Goji wine is enough.

132
00:05:26,220 --> 00:05:27,260
I don't need anything.

133
00:05:29,260 --> 00:05:30,430
- What about you?
- Fangfang,

134
00:05:30,660 --> 00:05:31,860
I actually need something.

135
00:05:36,100 --> 00:05:37,140
What do you need?

136
00:05:38,900 --> 00:05:39,980
Are you out of your mind?

137
00:05:39,980 --> 00:05:41,140
I'm not talking about that!

138
00:05:41,380 --> 00:05:42,300
Then what is it?

139
00:05:43,180 --> 00:05:44,810
I'm being serious!

140
00:05:45,220 --> 00:05:47,160
Fangfang, your husband

141
00:05:47,300 --> 00:05:48,370
is well-connected.

142
00:05:48,470 --> 00:05:50,020
He has great networks, right?

143
00:05:50,140 --> 00:05:51,780
Can he help me book a reservation

144
00:05:52,020 --> 00:05:53,740
at the Oriental Pearl
Revolving Restaurant?

145
00:05:55,980 --> 00:05:57,140
I thought…

146
00:05:58,380 --> 00:05:59,220
Wasn't you

147
00:05:59,220 --> 00:06:00,460
just complaining about

148
00:06:00,460 --> 00:06:01,860
how annoying another person is?

149
00:06:01,860 --> 00:06:02,900
Yet you still ask Fangfang

150
00:06:02,900 --> 00:06:03,940
to help you book a table.

151
00:06:04,940 --> 00:06:06,940
Xiu'e is all talk but soft-hearted.

152
00:06:07,040 --> 00:06:08,440
No matter what Chairwoman Liao asks,

153
00:06:08,440 --> 00:06:09,460
Xiu'e takes it to heart.

154
00:06:09,460 --> 00:06:10,300
Exactly.

155
00:06:10,420 --> 00:06:11,500
Just lower your expectations

156
00:06:11,500 --> 00:06:12,740
and relax a little.

157
00:06:13,380 --> 00:06:14,220
Alright.

158
00:06:14,420 --> 00:06:15,820
I'll handle it.

159
00:06:15,820 --> 00:06:16,740
I'll ask my husband.

160
00:06:21,820 --> 00:06:22,660
Chen,

161
00:06:23,180 --> 00:06:25,260
isn't it just a phone call?

162
00:06:29,220 --> 00:06:30,140
I remember

163
00:06:30,220 --> 00:06:31,580
last time when you went with

164
00:06:31,580 --> 00:06:32,820
Director Wang and others,

165
00:06:33,060 --> 00:06:34,860
you got it all sorted out
with just one call.

166
00:06:34,860 --> 00:06:36,220
What do you know?

167
00:06:36,420 --> 00:06:38,340
It's not as simple as
just making a phone call.

168
00:06:39,100 --> 00:06:40,380
There are a lot of people

169
00:06:40,380 --> 00:06:42,140
and politics involved. It's complicated.

170
00:06:42,680 --> 00:06:43,540
Fine, fine,

171
00:06:43,540 --> 00:06:44,900
I don't know much about it.

172
00:06:46,500 --> 00:06:48,180
But if it weren't for Chen Xiu'e,

173
00:06:48,180 --> 00:06:49,820
I wouldn't even be asking.

174
00:06:50,580 --> 00:06:52,340
This isn't just about her birthday.

175
00:06:52,340 --> 00:06:54,100
Her brothers are coming back
from the U.S.

176
00:06:54,380 --> 00:06:55,620
Her mom…

177
00:06:57,180 --> 00:06:58,660
You're really talkative.

178
00:06:59,420 --> 00:07:00,900
After spending so much time

179
00:07:00,990 --> 00:07:02,140
with these little people,

180
00:07:02,140 --> 00:07:03,660
you've really started to…

181
00:07:05,300 --> 00:07:06,140
Chen!

182
00:07:07,060 --> 00:07:08,340
I won't do this again, okay?

183
00:07:10,420 --> 00:07:11,260
Don't do this again.

184
00:07:11,820 --> 00:07:12,820
Just this once.

185
00:07:13,260 --> 00:07:14,460
Let me remind you,

186
00:07:14,740 --> 00:07:17,140
don't keep taking on
these favors for others.

187
00:07:17,420 --> 00:07:18,980
I know, I know.

188
00:07:18,980 --> 00:07:20,510
Look at you.

189
00:07:32,060 --> 00:07:33,140
Honey.

190
00:07:34,140 --> 00:07:35,380
I'm back.

191
00:07:36,060 --> 00:07:36,900
Xiu'e.

192
00:07:38,780 --> 00:07:39,740
You're back.

193
00:07:40,820 --> 00:07:41,660
Honey!

194
00:07:41,780 --> 00:07:42,780
What are you doing?

195
00:07:43,020 --> 00:07:44,860
The doctor said not to move too quickly.

196
00:07:44,860 --> 00:07:46,420
- I'm fine.
- Sit down, quickly!

197
00:07:46,740 --> 00:07:47,660
Listen to the doctor.

198
00:07:49,340 --> 00:07:50,260
This is from Mom.

199
00:07:55,020 --> 00:07:57,860
Why are you holding it?

200
00:07:57,860 --> 00:07:59,180
This is the extra 600 yuan.

201
00:08:00,140 --> 00:08:01,060
Two meals,

202
00:08:01,460 --> 00:08:02,580
both her treat.

203
00:08:02,780 --> 00:08:03,940
One for your birthday

204
00:08:03,990 --> 00:08:05,340
and one for your brothers' return.

205
00:08:06,140 --> 00:08:07,060
She's not biased.

206
00:08:11,820 --> 00:08:12,660
What?

207
00:08:12,670 --> 00:08:13,990
She finally had a change of heart.

208
00:08:16,460 --> 00:08:18,940
I've always been fair, okay?

209
00:08:19,460 --> 00:08:20,460
Mom, did you hear that?

210
00:08:20,460 --> 00:08:21,300
I did.

211
00:08:21,660 --> 00:08:22,940
Where's the bias?

212
00:08:22,990 --> 00:08:23,940
Who am I biased against?

213
00:08:29,820 --> 00:08:30,660
Honey,

214
00:08:31,420 --> 00:08:34,100
I've pulled some strings
to book the restaurant.

215
00:08:36,020 --> 00:08:38,100
You need connections
to book a restaurant?

216
00:08:38,380 --> 00:08:39,580
That's nonsense.

217
00:08:40,140 --> 00:08:41,660
What connections are you talking about?

218
00:08:43,740 --> 00:08:44,580
Honey,

219
00:08:44,860 --> 00:08:46,500
I, Chen Xiu'e,

220
00:08:46,620 --> 00:08:48,260
really have connections everywhere.

221
00:08:53,740 --> 00:08:54,580
Honey,

222
00:08:54,700 --> 00:08:56,100
give her back

223
00:08:56,380 --> 00:08:57,460
the extra money.

224
00:08:58,380 --> 00:08:59,220
We're family,

225
00:08:59,220 --> 00:09:00,700
there's no need to have two meals.

226
00:09:01,300 --> 00:09:02,380
Don't waste the money.

227
00:09:03,420 --> 00:09:04,260
Give it back.

228
00:09:10,620 --> 00:09:11,460
Mom,

229
00:09:11,660 --> 00:09:12,660
Xiu'e said

230
00:09:13,260 --> 00:09:15,420
we only need one meal,

231
00:09:15,420 --> 00:09:16,460
no need to waste money.

232
00:09:18,420 --> 00:09:19,380
I know.

233
00:09:23,620 --> 00:09:25,260
I've already collected the quilts.

234
00:09:25,620 --> 00:09:26,340
Tell her

235
00:09:26,520 --> 00:09:27,980
to help me put the quilt covers on.

236
00:09:34,300 --> 00:09:35,140
Xiu'e,

237
00:09:35,460 --> 00:09:36,340
Mom wants you

238
00:09:36,340 --> 00:09:38,020
to help her with the quilt covers.

239
00:09:39,140 --> 00:09:40,580
I need to get changed first.

240
00:09:43,980 --> 00:09:48,260
(Class 5, Grade 10)

241
00:09:54,530 --> 00:09:55,410
Dust.

242
00:09:55,420 --> 00:09:57,380
But… who's even going to touch that?

243
00:09:57,380 --> 00:09:58,580
We'll correct it right now.

244
00:10:00,640 --> 00:10:01,900
There's dust,
minus two points.

245
00:10:02,540 --> 00:10:04,180
Please! If you deduct two points,

246
00:10:04,180 --> 00:10:05,990
- we'll lose our mobile red banner!
- Exactly!

247
00:10:05,990 --> 00:10:07,100
Please, give us a break!

248
00:10:08,300 --> 00:10:09,260
Look, look!

249
00:10:09,260 --> 00:10:10,660
Everywhere else is clean.

250
00:10:10,660 --> 00:10:11,740
It's just that spot

251
00:10:11,740 --> 00:10:13,340
because I can't reach it.

252
00:10:13,580 --> 00:10:14,580
You saw it,

253
00:10:14,580 --> 00:10:16,340
the door, the wood,

254
00:10:16,340 --> 00:10:17,980
and everywhere else is spotless.

255
00:10:19,980 --> 00:10:20,820
Please…

256
00:10:21,740 --> 00:10:22,740
The dust was noticed.

257
00:10:22,740 --> 00:10:24,260
- Help us out.
- I promise

258
00:10:25,220 --> 00:10:27,260
there won't be dust next time.

259
00:10:27,260 --> 00:10:28,540
We'll wipe it clean!

260
00:10:28,540 --> 00:10:29,460
Excuse me.

261
00:10:29,740 --> 00:10:30,580
The thing is,

262
00:10:30,660 --> 00:10:31,290
the door frame

263
00:10:31,290 --> 00:10:32,380
is too high for us to reach.

264
00:10:32,740 --> 00:10:33,580
Well,

265
00:10:33,740 --> 00:10:35,220
let me clean it now.

266
00:10:40,740 --> 00:10:41,820
See? No more dust.

267
00:10:42,380 --> 00:10:43,460
We'll clean it next time.

268
00:10:43,780 --> 00:10:44,740
We'll correct it.

269
00:10:44,740 --> 00:10:45,620
We'll be more careful.

270
00:10:47,740 --> 00:10:48,820
- Miss?
- Miss?

271
00:10:50,220 --> 00:10:51,060
Well…

272
00:10:51,140 --> 00:10:52,660
make sure to be more careful next time.

273
00:10:52,780 --> 00:10:54,460
- We will.
- Of course we will.

274
00:10:56,740 --> 00:10:57,580
Goodbye!

275
00:10:57,580 --> 00:10:58,500
- Bye!
- Thank you!

276
00:10:58,940 --> 00:11:00,380
Thanks! I'll buy you a drink!

277
00:11:01,140 --> 00:11:01,980
Chen Mo!

278
00:11:01,980 --> 00:11:03,260
How are you even on duty?

279
00:11:03,380 --> 00:11:04,380
Be careful next time!

280
00:11:04,380 --> 00:11:05,220
I… I…

281
00:11:06,180 --> 00:11:07,020
Lu Yao,

282
00:11:07,180 --> 00:11:08,460
thanks to you,

283
00:11:08,580 --> 00:11:10,300
we were able to keep
the mobile red banner.

284
00:11:11,020 --> 00:11:11,860
Thanks to you.

285
00:11:11,860 --> 00:11:12,700
No problem.

286
00:11:15,420 --> 00:11:16,340
What are you buying me?

287
00:11:16,740 --> 00:11:17,620
How about cola?

288
00:11:19,220 --> 00:11:20,060
Everyone,

289
00:11:21,580 --> 00:11:22,940
I have something to announce

290
00:11:22,940 --> 00:11:23,900
during break time.

