Read the first sentence

872
00:36:01,220 --> 00:36:02,620
as a whole.

873
00:36:08,060 --> 00:36:10,180
Your pass...

874
00:36:11,020 --> 00:36:13,340
Take it out... Let me...

875
00:36:14,700 --> 00:36:15,540
See... see.

876
00:36:17,300 --> 00:36:18,540
Wrong for "pass"!

877
00:36:18,860 --> 00:36:20,260
And wrong for "see see"!

878
00:36:21,380 --> 00:36:22,220
Never mind.

879
00:36:22,380 --> 00:36:23,860
Baby, where are you going?

880
00:36:24,340 --> 00:36:25,070
Half an hour...

881
00:36:25,070 --> 00:36:26,860
Mom, I've been teaching you
for half an hour,

882
00:36:26,860 --> 00:36:28,780
and you still can't get two words right!

883
00:36:29,500 --> 00:36:30,540
I'll learn it right away.

884
00:36:30,540 --> 00:36:31,540
I will!

885
00:36:31,540 --> 00:36:33,300
Baby, persistence is key!

886
00:36:33,580 --> 00:36:34,420
Mom,

887
00:36:34,420 --> 00:36:35,620
just stop persisting.

888
00:36:53,500 --> 00:36:54,340
Alright.

889
00:36:54,700 --> 00:36:56,460
What's this fruit?

890
00:36:56,940 --> 00:36:57,780
Apple.

891
00:36:58,140 --> 00:36:59,740
How do you say the juice made from it?

892
00:36:59,980 --> 00:37:01,020
Just remember...

893
00:37:01,660 --> 00:37:02,980
apple juice.

894
00:37:02,990 --> 00:37:03,860
Why?

895
00:37:03,860 --> 00:37:06,060
Because God-grandma likes apples.

896
00:37:06,060 --> 00:37:07,460
Her other name sounds like apple.

897
00:37:07,460 --> 00:37:09,130
So when you think of her,
think of apples.

898
00:37:09,300 --> 00:37:11,340
And the juice? Apple juice.

899
00:37:11,740 --> 00:37:13,140
Apple juice!

900
00:37:13,140 --> 00:37:14,140
That's a good method.

901
00:37:14,140 --> 00:37:14,980
Godmother.

902
00:37:15,580 --> 00:37:16,540
Now, watermelon juice.

903
00:37:16,540 --> 00:37:17,540
Repeat after me.

904
00:37:17,540 --> 00:37:18,700
Watermelon juice.

905
00:37:19,100 --> 00:37:20,700
Watermelon juice.

906
00:37:20,700 --> 00:37:23,340
How to memorize it... Watermelon...

907
00:37:23,340 --> 00:37:24,660
My head is gone!

908
00:37:25,660 --> 00:37:26,660
No, no!

909
00:37:26,660 --> 00:37:27,540
That's too bloody!

910
00:37:28,420 --> 00:37:29,460
Bloody? Exactly!

911
00:37:29,460 --> 00:37:30,760
What color is blood? Red, right?

912
00:37:30,800 --> 00:37:32,140
So is the flesh of watermelon.

913
00:37:32,420 --> 00:37:33,260
It matches!

914
00:37:34,140 --> 00:37:35,940
I'll never drink watermelon juice again.

915
00:37:37,100 --> 00:37:38,140
Mrs. Xiao.

916
00:37:38,500 --> 00:37:39,860
How do you pronounce orange juice?

917
00:37:41,740 --> 00:37:43,380
Orange juice.

918
00:37:45,660 --> 00:37:46,500
Very standard!

919
00:37:48,100 --> 00:37:49,980
Han taught me that yesterday.

920
00:37:50,420 --> 00:37:51,500
Impressive.

921
00:37:51,700 --> 00:37:52,740
Oh, Mr. Zhang,

922
00:37:52,740 --> 00:37:54,220
there's one I didn't catch.

923
00:37:54,780 --> 00:37:55,620
Tomato.

924
00:37:55,790 --> 00:37:57,420
How do you say tomato juice?

925
00:37:58,100 --> 00:37:59,060
Tomato...

926
00:37:59,800 --> 00:38:01,180
tomato juice is just tomato juice.

927
00:38:01,180 --> 00:38:02,260
The pronunciation is...

928
00:38:02,260 --> 00:38:04,260
Enough, enough. Mao Tou, stop teaching us

929
00:38:04,260 --> 00:38:05,540
about fruit juices.

930
00:38:05,540 --> 00:38:07,580
Why not teach us
something more practical?

931
00:38:07,580 --> 00:38:08,580
Exactly.

932
00:38:08,580 --> 00:38:09,900
We want to be flight attendants.

933
00:38:09,900 --> 00:38:11,460
We won't need to know this stuff.

934
00:38:11,940 --> 00:38:12,580
How come?

935
00:38:12,580 --> 00:38:13,860
Don't you have to serve drinks

936
00:38:13,860 --> 00:38:15,060
to passengers on the plane?

937
00:38:15,060 --> 00:38:16,060
When you ask them,

938
00:38:16,060 --> 00:38:17,540
how do you do it? Answer me.

939
00:38:18,500 --> 00:38:20,620
Excuse me, sir.

940
00:38:21,100 --> 00:38:23,540
Do you want anything to drink?

941
00:38:24,460 --> 00:38:25,500
Apple juice,

942
00:38:25,860 --> 00:38:27,180
orange juice,

943
00:38:27,180 --> 00:38:28,940
watermelon juice,

944
00:38:29,180 --> 00:38:31,180
hot tea, or coffee?

945
00:38:31,540 --> 00:38:34,140
Which one do you prefer?

946
00:38:37,300 --> 00:38:38,140
Do you what?

947
00:38:38,260 --> 00:38:39,300
Prefer.

948
00:38:39,540 --> 00:38:40,780
Prefer?

949
00:38:41,700 --> 00:38:42,660
Han taught me that.

950
00:38:42,860 --> 00:38:43,780
He said

951
00:38:43,780 --> 00:38:45,340
using "prefer" here sounds better

952
00:38:45,340 --> 00:38:46,300
than "want".

953
00:38:46,300 --> 00:38:47,140
It's...

954
00:38:47,780 --> 00:38:48,980
more native.

955
00:38:52,180 --> 00:38:53,460
Impressive, Aiping!

956
00:38:53,460 --> 00:38:54,300
A divine text!

957
00:38:54,300 --> 00:38:57,540
(Shanghai Puyang No. 2 Middle School)

958
00:38:57,540 --> 00:38:58,460
Air stewardess?

959
00:38:59,100 --> 00:38:59,940
Yeah.

960
00:39:00,340 --> 00:39:01,580
With my mom's abilities,

961
00:39:01,580 --> 00:39:02,940
I have no idea what she's thinking.

962
00:39:03,300 --> 00:39:04,300
Qian Jiayue,

963
00:39:04,980 --> 00:39:06,180
at least your mom...

964
00:39:08,560 --> 00:39:09,440
Right?

965
00:39:09,460 --> 00:39:10,300
My mom...

966
00:39:11,300 --> 00:39:12,700
She's just jumping on the bandwagon.

967
00:39:13,020 --> 00:39:14,560
But what if they get selected?

968
00:39:14,560 --> 00:39:16,100
Being a flight attendant would be great!

969
00:39:16,500 --> 00:39:18,380
Good pay, a decent job,

970
00:39:18,380 --> 00:39:19,620
nice uniforms,

971
00:39:19,620 --> 00:39:21,340
and you get to travel abroad
all the time.

972
00:39:22,340 --> 00:39:23,820
Why isn't my mom applying?

973
00:39:24,100 --> 00:39:25,780
If my mom gets selected,

974
00:39:26,060 --> 00:39:27,540
she'll make more money than my dad.

975
00:39:27,780 --> 00:39:28,980
Then my mom and I won't have to

976
00:39:28,980 --> 00:39:30,420
deal with my dad's mood anymore!

977
00:39:30,980 --> 00:39:31,980
That's why

978
00:39:32,340 --> 00:39:33,340
I think

979
00:39:33,340 --> 00:39:35,140
your mom and Mrs. Xiao

980
00:39:35,300 --> 00:39:37,020
are the two who should definitely apply.

981
00:39:37,900 --> 00:39:39,380
Does Xiao Han support his mom?

982
00:39:39,740 --> 00:39:40,860
He does.

983
00:39:40,860 --> 00:39:42,620
I heard Mrs. Xiao learns English

984
00:39:42,620 --> 00:39:44,220
so quickly and seriously,

985
00:39:44,700 --> 00:39:45,620
unlike my mom,

986
00:39:45,780 --> 00:39:46,680
who just babbles on

987
00:39:46,680 --> 00:39:47,820
and still can't get it right.

988
00:39:48,460 --> 00:39:49,660
By the way, Ka Men,

989
00:39:49,860 --> 00:39:50,600
did you sign up

990
00:39:50,600 --> 00:39:51,820
for the English host selection?

991
00:39:52,060 --> 00:39:52,900
Did you?

992
00:39:52,980 --> 00:39:53,900
Not yet.

993
00:39:54,700 --> 00:39:56,820
Didn't you say
you'd sign up a long time ago?

994
00:39:59,300 --> 00:40:00,500
I won't sign up

995
00:40:00,940 --> 00:40:02,710
unless I lose 5 kg!

996
00:40:03,060 --> 00:40:04,380
Qian Jiayue, Chen Mo,

997
00:40:04,660 --> 00:40:06,180
you both need to supervise me

998
00:40:06,180 --> 00:40:07,460
- Okay.
- and be strict with me.

999
00:40:08,580 --> 00:40:10,100
Then... ten squats.

1000
00:40:10,460 --> 00:40:11,300
Fifteen!

1001
00:40:11,620 --> 00:40:12,460
Okay.

1002
00:40:13,580 --> 00:40:14,900
One.

1003
00:40:16,300 --> 00:40:17,140
Wait.

1004
00:40:21,540 --> 00:40:22,380
Two.

1005
00:40:24,100 --> 00:40:25,530
Three.

1006
00:40:27,380 --> 00:40:28,220
Four?

1007
00:40:30,260 --> 00:40:31,100
What's going on?

1008
00:40:31,260 --> 00:40:32,260
Let's take a break.

1009
00:41:04,660 --> 00:41:06,700
One, two, three.

1010
00:41:08,500 --> 00:41:11,700
Curl your hands... Pose!

1011
00:41:11,940 --> 00:41:13,390
Bring your feet together.

1012
00:41:14,420 --> 00:41:15,260
One.

1013
00:41:15,860 --> 00:41:16,700
Two.

1014
00:41:17,260 --> 00:41:18,180
Three.

1015
00:41:18,180 --> 00:41:19,660
Cross your legs.

1016
00:41:19,900 --> 00:41:24,460
Open. Push your hands. Curl them!

1017
00:41:25,140 --> 00:41:25,980
Look.

1018
00:41:27,180 --> 00:41:28,020
Good!

1019
00:41:29,540 --> 00:41:30,380
Pei.

1020
00:41:30,660 --> 00:41:31,500
Pei?

1021
00:41:32,140 --> 00:41:33,200
You're here.

1022
00:41:35,700 --> 00:41:36,620
You are...

1023
00:41:38,900 --> 00:41:41,540
I... I'm here to pick up
the recommendation letter.

1024
00:41:41,860 --> 00:41:43,620
The stamp for the letter
is already on it.

1025
00:41:43,860 --> 00:41:45,060
Follow me, I'll give it to you.

1026
00:41:45,340 --> 00:41:46,970
You're responding to the 4050 Initiative

1027
00:41:46,970 --> 00:41:47,900
to be an air stewardess.

1028
00:41:48,100 --> 00:41:49,860
We definitely support you.

1029
00:41:51,300 --> 00:41:53,420
(Jiale Wontons)
Glad to have you. This is Sunny Club.

1030
00:41:53,460 --> 00:41:54,900
At the end of the program,

1031
00:41:54,900 --> 00:41:57,060
as usual, we'll read
a letter from a viewer.

1032
00:41:58,060 --> 00:42:00,540
A student named Tianyou
from Putuo District

1033
00:42:00,700 --> 00:42:02,860
wants to share his recent study insights.

1034
00:42:04,060 --> 00:42:04,940
"This semester,

1035
00:42:05,100 --> 00:42:07,420
I've focused on the subjects I'm not good at.

1036
00:42:07,420 --> 00:42:09,540
In Chinese subject,
besides mastering the content

1037
00:42:09,540 --> 00:42:10,620
in the textbook..."

1038
00:42:10,620 --> 00:42:11,460
I'm back.

1039
00:42:12,940 --> 00:42:13,820
Keep going.

1040
00:42:14,620 --> 00:42:15,460
Pei,

1041
00:42:15,560 --> 00:42:16,660
you're not cooking, right?

1042
00:42:17,060 --> 00:42:17,900
I won't either.

1043
00:42:17,900 --> 00:42:19,460
I'm heading to Food Republic for dinner.

1044
00:42:23,780 --> 00:42:24,700
Where's your mom?

1045
00:42:24,700 --> 00:42:25,540
She's not home.

1046
00:42:25,740 --> 00:42:26,580
Where did she go?

1047
00:42:27,340 --> 00:42:28,180
I don't know.

1048
00:42:30,380 --> 00:42:31,220
You're back.

1049
00:42:32,500 --> 00:42:33,460
What did you buy?

1050
00:42:35,260 --> 00:42:36,340
Did you go to the mall?

1051
00:42:39,660 --> 00:42:40,860
It says "clothing".

1052
00:42:41,420 --> 00:42:42,260
Clothing, huh?

1053
00:42:46,460 --> 00:42:47,700
It isn't for me, though.

1054
00:42:48,900 --> 00:42:49,860
What is it for?

1055
00:42:51,380 --> 00:42:53,140
The air stewardess selection.

1056
00:42:53,700 --> 00:42:54,940
Seriously?

1057
00:42:55,700 --> 00:42:57,780
That color will make you look bigger!

1058
00:43:19,180 --> 00:43:20,020
What's wrong?

1059
00:43:20,160 --> 00:43:21,020
I'm not wrong.

1060
00:43:21,020 --> 00:43:22,930
That color will definitely
make her look bigger.

